	<p id="general"><b>GENERAL TERMS:</b> Offers and rates apply to business customers only. The following section applies to all business services.</p>
	<p><b>GENERAL:</b> Services and offers not available everywhere. CenturyLink may change or cancel services, or substitute similar services at its sole discretion without notice. Requires credit approval and deposit may be required. Additional restrictions apply.</p>
	<p><b>TERMS AND CONDITIONS:</b> All products and services are governed by tariffs, terms of service, or terms and conditions posted at <a href="http://www.centurylink.com/Pages/AboutUs/Legal/">http://www.centurylink.com/Pages/AboutUs/Legal/</a> ("Website"). Products and services are provided by the CenturyLink operating company serving your service location. </p>
	<p><b>TAXES, FEES, AND SURCHARGES:</b> All prices exclude taxes, fees and surcharges, which apply to all services, and include federal and state-mandated and permitted charges, cost recovery charges, state and local fees that vary by area, and certain in-state surcharges. Cost recovery fees are not taxes or government-required charges use. Additional charges apply depending on services selected, including a carrier Universal Service charge, carrier cost recovery surcharges or national access fee surcharge, and a one-time High-speed Internet activation fee. Taxes, fees, and surcharges apply based on standard monthly, not promotional, rates. </p>
	<p><b>MONTHLY RATE:</b> Monthly rate applies while customer subscribes to all qualifying services. If one or more services are cancelled, the standard monthly rate will apply to each remaining service. </p>
	<p><b>DISCOUNTS AND CREDITS:</b> All applicable discounts and credits will be applied beginning in the first or second full month of billing.</p>
	<p id="specific"><b>SERVICE AND OFFER-SPECIFIC TERMS:</b> Each section below applies to the specific business service listed. Subscription to specific services or offers by existing customers will cause the loss of any then-current discounts related to such services purchased.</p>
	<p id="phone"><b>LOCAL SERVICES:</b> Local phone services include direct-dial, local calling, a number of calling features determined by the selected local service plan, and choice of CenturyLink long distance plans (additional charges apply). Plans exclude dial-up internet connections, conference lines, directory and operator assistance, multi-party conference calls, or other non single path person to person conversation or voice message. CenturyLink reserves the right to move a customer on this plan to an alternative plan if usage on the plan does not resemble typical business, local voice calling. </p>
	<p><b>LONG DISTANCE SERVICES:</b> Per minute and monthly recurring rates apply to one business phone line with direct-dial, nationwide voice calling; including all U.S. states, Puerto Rico, Guam, and US Virgin Islands; excludes data and facsimile services (including dial-up internet connections), conference lines, directory and operator assistance, chat lines, pay-per-call, calling card use, transcriptions, or multi-dwelling units. Restrictions on number of local and long-distance packages/plans per account apply. CenturyLink reserves the right to move a customer on the plan to an alternative plan if usage on the plan does not resemble typical business usage. International calling available for additional per minute and/or per month charges; all applicable rates are posted to the Website. If a block of minutes is included for long distance calling, the following applies: block minutes do not apply to operator services, switched data services or international calls; usage in excess of block minutes are billed at the applicable per minute rate; unused minutes in the block do not carry over to next month; and all International calling is billing separately from block minutes. </p>
	<p id="internet"><b>HIGH-SPEED INTERNET SERVICES:</b> Speed availability varies by service location. A term commitment (12 months, 24 months, or 36 months) may be required and depending on customer location, early termination results in either a $199 early termination fee or payment of the applicable monthly recurring service fee multiplied by the number of months remaining in the minimum service period, up to $200. An additional monthly fee (including professional installation, if applicable) and a shipping and handling fee will apply to customer's modem or router. Performance will vary due to conditions outside of network control and no speed is guaranteed. Consistent speed claim and private direct connection claim as well as claim that your connection to CenturyLink's network is 100% yours is based on CenturyLink providing HSI subscribers with a dedicated virtual circuit connection to the CenturyLink central office.</p>
	<p><b>BUSINESS SUPPORT PACK:</b> Rates listed are per computer, per month with a 12-month term. Early termination fees apply. Microsoft Windows 2000, 7, XP or Vista operating systems only. Suspected misuse or abuse of any computer support may result in termination of support. CenturyLink reserves the right to limit the amount of time spent on any single issue and recommend the dispatch of an in-office technician, at additional cost to customer, in order to resolve the issue, any may decline certain services or operations outside of the scope of the service defined in the Terms and Conditions. RescueIT In-Office Computer Support: Additional charges will apply. Microsoft Windows 2000, 7, XP, Vista or Apply operating systems installation, reinstallation or system recovery only. All necessary connections require customer-supplied wiring and adaptors. </p>
	<p><b>RESCUEIT FREE SETUP OFFER:</b> One personal computer per plan. 12-month term agreement required. Early termination fees apply in the total amount of monthly recurring charges remaining in the term.  Microsoft Windows&reg; 2000, XP, Windows 7 or Vista operating systems only. Suspected misuse or abuse of any computer support may result in termination of support. CenturyLink reserves the right to limit the amount of time spent on any single issue and recommend the dispatch of an in-office technician, at additional costs to customer, in order to resolve the issue, and may decline certain services or operations outside of the scope of the service defined in the Terms and Conditions. In-Office Computer Support:  Microsoft Windows&reg; 2000, XP, Windows 7 or Vista or Apple operating systems installation, reinstallation or system recovery only. All necessary connections require customer-supplied wiring and adaptors.</p>
	<p><b>HIGH-SPEED INTERNET OFFER:</b> Listed rate available to new High-Speed Internet business customers subscribing to speed tiers from 1.5 to 10mbps. Minimum 24-month term commitment for High-Speed Internet required and requires subscription to a qualifying calling plan from CenturyLink. Price after sixth month will vary by speed tier and length of selected High-Speed Internet term commitment. Requires subscription to qualifying CenturyLink calling plan. Depending on customer location, early termination results in either a $199 early termination fee or payment of the applicable monthly recurring service fee multiplied by the number of months remaining in the minimum service period, up to $200. </p>
	<p><b>PURE BROADBAND OFFER:</b> The listed High-Speed Internet discount rate is available to new PURE Broadband business customers only and requires a 24-month term agreement (after 12 months the rate reverts to the then-current standard rate). Listed rate applies to speed tiers of 3 to 10 mbps High-Speed Internet service. Not combinable with other offers. An additional monthly fee (including professional installation, if applicable) and separate shipping and handling fee will apply to customer's modem or router. Depending on customer location, either a $99 early termination fee will apply or customer will be responsible for payment of the applicable monthly recurring service fee multiplied by the number of months remaining in the minimum service period, up to $200.00. Performance will vary due to conditions outside of network control and no speed is guaranteed. Telephone landline is part of the service only for the purpose of data traffic transmission/connection and cannot be used for voice traffic transmission, except for 911 services.</p>
	<p id="solutions"><b>CORE CONNECT BUNDLE OFFER:</b> The listed bundle monthly rate includes high-speed Internet with speed tiers from 1.5 to 10 mbps depending on availability, unlimited direct-dial local and domestic long-distance service and requires a 36-month term agreement (after which the rate reverts to the then-current standard rate). An additional monthly fee (including professional installation, if applicable) and separate shipping and handling fee will apply to customer's modem or router. Depending on customer location, early termination results in either a $199 early termination fee or payment of the applicable monthly recurring service fee multiplied by the number of months remaining in the minimum service period, up to $200. Service-specific terms set forth in the local, long distance and high-speed Internet service paragraphs above also apply.</p>
	<p><b>Core Connect bundle discount</b> - Customer will receive one service credit each month on the HSI portion of the invoice for 12 consecutive months beginning with the first or second invoice.</p>
	<p><b>TRIPLE BIZ BUNDLE OFFER:</b> The listed bundle monthly rate includes high-speed Internet with speed tiers from 1.5 to 10 mbps depending on availability, unlimited direct-dial local and domestic long-distance service, and DIRECTV Business Information service package and requires a 36- month term agreement for CenturyLink services and a 24-month term agreement for DIRECTV (after 12 months the rates revert to the then-current standard rate). An additional monthly fee (including professional installation, if applicable) and separate shipping and handling fee will apply to customer's modem or router. Depending on customer location, early termination results in either a $199 early termination fee or payment of the applicable monthly recurring service fee multiplied by the number of months remaining in the minimum service period, up to $200. Service-specific terms set forth in the local, long distance, high-speed Internet service paragraphs above and the DIRECTV offer paragraphs also apply.</p>
	<p><b>GROW PACK OFFER:</b> Business Customers with CenturyLink High-Speed Internet and Office Plus or Core Connect only. Grow Essentials: Listed monthly rate is for a month-to-month term and includes the listed features. Grow Complete: Listed monthly rate includes listed features, requires a 12-month term and a one-time $300 set-up fee. One website design per plan. Suspected misuse or abuse of any website maintenance support may result in termination of support. Customer may incur additional costs for additional maintenance time over the included 30 minutes per month. Early termination fees: If customer terminates before end of term, customer will receive a full refund for termination within 30 days from order date if no pre-development work has begun. If pre-development work has begun, and customer is still within the first 30 days after order date, customer will receive a 50% refund. For early termination after 30 days or after development has begun, an early termination charge equal to the monthly recurring charge for any months remaining in the term, plus any charges for services accrued but not yet paid will apply. </p>
